# 🚀 ProjectLauncher — Build a Desktop-Grade AI Project Manager with Claude Code
### A Complete Step-by-Step Guide using Task Master AI · Roo Code · MCP · Free AI APIs

---

## 📋 Table of Contents

1. [What We're Building](#1-what-were-building)
2. [Prerequisites & System Requirements](#2-prerequisites--system-requirements)
3. [Install Claude Code & Recommended Extensions](#3-install-claude-code--recommended-extensions)
4. [Set Up Your Workspace Structure](#4-set-up-your-workspace-structure)
5. [Install Task Master AI (MCP)](#5-install-task-master-ai-mcp)
6. [Configure Your Free AI API (OpenRouter / NVIDIA / Gemini)](#6-configure-your-free-ai-api-openrouter--nvidia--gemini)
7. [Create the Electron Desktop App Shell](#7-create-the-electron-desktop-app-shell)
8. [Build the UI with Roo Code + UX Pro Max Design System](#8-build-the-ui-with-roo-code--ux-pro-max-design-system)
9. [Build the AI Project Scanner Engine](#9-build-the-ai-project-scanner-engine)
10. [Wire Up: Install Requirements Button](#10-wire-up-install-requirements-button)
11. [Wire Up: Start Project Button](#11-wire-up-start-project-button)
12. [Add the File/Folder Browser (Native OS Dialog)](#12-add-the-filefolder-browser-native-os-dialog)
13. [Task Master AI Workflow Integration](#13-task-master-ai-workflow-integration)
14. [Dot Mac (.mdc) Rules Configuration](#14-dot-mac-mdc-rules-configuration)
15. [Polish: Animations, Themes & Micro-interactions](#15-polish-animations-themes--micro-interactions)
16. [Test, Build & Package as a Desktop App](#16-test-build--package-as-a-desktop-app)
17. [Marketplace Extensions to Install](#17-marketplace-extensions-to-install)
18. [Final Folder Structure](#18-final-folder-structure)
19. [Troubleshooting](#19-troubleshooting)

---

## 1. What We're Building

A **native desktop application** (Electron + React) that:

- Lets you **click-browse** your PC for any project folder
- **AI-scans** the folder (read-only) using a free AI model via OpenRouter / NVIDIA NIM / Gemini
- Automatically **detects** `requirements.txt`, `main.py`, `app.py`, `manage.py`, `index.js`, etc.
- Exposes two clean buttons: **▶ Install Requirements** and **⚡ Start Project**
- Streams **live terminal output** inside the UI
- Is **fully themed** with a dark, industrial-futuristic aesthetic using Roo Code's design tokens
- Uses **Task Master AI** to manage the build process itself (so Claude Code builds this app step-by-step intelligently)

**Stack:** Electron · React · Vite · Node.js · Python bridge · Task Master AI MCP · Free AI API

---

## 2. Prerequisites & System Requirements

### Required Software

```bash
# Check versions before starting
node --version       # Need v18+
npm --version        # Need v9+
python --version     # Need 3.8+
git --version        # Any recent version
```

### Install Node.js (if not installed)
```
https://nodejs.org → Download LTS version (v20 recommended)
```

### Install Python (if not installed)
```
https://python.org → Download 3.11+ (check "Add to PATH" on Windows)
```

### Operating System
| OS | Status |
|---|---|
| Windows 10/11 | ✅ Fully supported |
| macOS 12+ | ✅ Fully supported |
| Ubuntu 20.04+ | ✅ Fully supported |

---

## 3. Install Claude Code & Recommended Extensions

### Step 3.1 — Install Claude Code (CLI)

```bash
npm install -g @anthropic-ai/claude-code
```

Verify:
```bash
claude --version
```

### Step 3.2 — Install VS Code (if you want the editor too)

```
https://code.visualstudio.com
```

### Step 3.3 — Essential VS Code Marketplace Extensions

Install these in VS Code (`Ctrl+Shift+X` → search each name):

| Extension | Publisher | Why You Need It |
|---|---|---|
| **Roo Code** | RooVeterinaryInc | AI-powered code agent with UX design awareness |
| **Tailwind CSS IntelliSense** | Bradlc | Autocomplete for Tailwind classes |
| **Prettier** | Prettier | Auto-formats all your code |
| **ESLint** | Microsoft | Catches JS/React bugs |
| **Python** | Microsoft | Python syntax + linting |
| **Auto Rename Tag** | Jun Han | Rename HTML/JSX tags together |
| **Path Intellisense** | Christian Kohler | Autocomplete for file paths |
| **Better Comments** | Aaron Bond | Color-coded TODO/NOTE/FIXME |
| **Error Lens** | Alexander | Inline error messages |
| **GitLens** | GitKraken | Git history inline |
| **vscode-icons** | VSCode Icons Team | Project file icons |
| **Thunder Client** | Ranga Vadhineni | Test APIs without Postman |
| **DotENV** | mikestead | `.env` file syntax highlighting |

### Step 3.4 — Install Roo Code Extension

In VS Code:
1. Press `Ctrl+Shift+X`
2. Search: `Roo Code`
3. Click **Install**
4. After install → click **Roo Code icon** in left sidebar
5. Set your preferred AI provider (we'll use OpenRouter — see Section 6)

---

## 4. Set Up Your Workspace Structure

### Step 4.1 — Create the Project

```bash
mkdir project-launcher
cd project-launcher
git init
```

### Step 4.2 — Open in Claude Code

```bash
claude
```

This opens an interactive Claude Code session in your terminal. Claude can now read, write, and run code in this folder.

### Step 4.3 — Open in VS Code as well

```bash
code .
```

You'll work in **both terminals** — Claude Code CLI for AI-driven tasks, VS Code for visual editing and Roo Code.

---

## 5. Install Task Master AI (MCP)

Task Master AI breaks your big project into smart subtasks and manages them through Claude Code.

### Step 5.1 — Install Task Master AI globally

```bash
npm install -g task-master-ai
```

### Step 5.2 — Configure MCP in Claude Code

Create the MCP config file:

```bash
# In your project root
mkdir -p .claude
```

Create `.claude/mcp.json`:

```json
{
  "mcpServers": {
    "taskmaster-ai": {
      "command": "npx",
      "args": ["-y", "--package=task-master-ai", "task-master-ai"],
      "env": {
        "ANTHROPIC_API_KEY": "your_anthropic_key_here",
        "OPENROUTER_API_KEY": "your_openrouter_key_here",
        "MODEL": "claude-sonnet-4-20250514",
        "MAIN_MODEL": "claude-sonnet-4-20250514",
        "RESEARCH_MODEL": "openrouter/google/gemini-flash-1.5",
        "FALLBACK_MODEL": "openrouter/meta-llama/llama-3.1-8b-instruct:free"
      }
    }
  }
}
```

### Step 5.3 — Initialize Task Master in your project

Inside Claude Code session (`claude` command):

```
/mcp
```

Confirm Task Master is connected. Then:

```
Initialize taskmaster-ai for a new project called "ProjectLauncher"
```

This creates a `tasks/` folder and `tasks.json` scaffold.

### Step 5.4 — Create your PRD (Product Requirements Document)

Create `scripts/prd.txt`:

```
# ProjectLauncher — PRD

## Overview
A desktop Electron app that lets users browse their PC for any Python/Node project folder,
uses a free AI API to scan the project (read-only), detects the entry point and requirements file,
then presents two action buttons: Install Requirements and Start Project.

## Core Features
1. Native folder browser dialog (OS-level)
2. AI project scanner (OpenRouter free tier or Gemini free tier)
3. requirements.txt / package.json / pyproject.toml auto-detection
4. Entry point detection (main.py, app.py, manage.py, index.js, server.js)
5. Install Requirements button → runs pip install or npm install with live streaming output
6. Start Project button → runs detected start command with live streaming output
7. Dark industrial UI with animated terminal output panel
8. Persistent project history (last 10 projects)

## Tech Stack
- Electron 28+ (desktop shell)
- React 18 + Vite (UI)
- Tailwind CSS (styling)
- Node.js IPC bridge (main ↔ renderer)
- child_process (running pip/npm/python commands)
- OpenRouter API or Gemini API (free AI scanning)
```

Now ask Task Master to parse it:

```
task-master parse-prd scripts/prd.txt
```

Task Master will generate structured tasks. View them:

```
task-master list
```

You'll see numbered tasks like:
- Task 1: Set up Electron + React + Vite boilerplate
- Task 2: Build folder browser component
- Task 3: Build AI scanner module
- Task 4: Build terminal output panel
- etc.

---

## 6. Configure Your Free AI API (OpenRouter / NVIDIA / Gemini)

You only need **ONE** of these. Pick the easiest for you.

### Option A — OpenRouter (RECOMMENDED — Most Free Models)

1. Go to: `https://openrouter.ai`
2. Sign up (free)
3. Go to **Keys** → Create API Key
4. Free models available:
   - `google/gemini-flash-1.5` — fast, smart, generous free tier
   - `meta-llama/llama-3.1-8b-instruct:free` — completely free
   - `microsoft/phi-3-mini-128k-instruct:free` — great for code analysis

5. Copy your key: `[REDACTED_KEY]`

### Option B — Google Gemini (Free Tier)

1. Go to: `https://aistudio.google.com`
2. Sign in with Google
3. Click **Get API Key**
4. Free tier: Gemini 1.5 Flash — 15 requests/minute, 1M tokens/day
5. Copy your key: `[REDACTED_KEY]`

### Option C — NVIDIA NIM (Free Credits on Sign-up)

1. Go to: `https://build.nvidia.com`
2. Sign up → get 1000 free API credits
3. Use models like `meta/llama-3.1-8b-instruct`
4. Copy your key: `nvapi-xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx`

### Create your `.env` file

In project root, create `.env`:

```env
# Pick ONE provider and fill it in

# OpenRouter (recommended)
OPENROUTER_API_KEY=[REDACTED_KEY] OR Gemini
GEMINI_API_KEY=[REDACTED_KEY] OR NVIDIA NIM
NVIDIA_API_KEY=nvapi-your-key-here
NVIDIA_BASE_URL=https://integrate.api.nvidia.com/v1
NVIDIA_MODEL=meta/llama-3.1-8b-instruct

# App settings
MAX_SCAN_DEPTH=5
MAX_FILES_TO_SCAN=50
```

> ⚠️ Add `.env` to your `.gitignore` immediately — never commit API keys.

```bash
echo ".env" >> .gitignore
```

---

## 7. Create the Electron Desktop App Shell

